20MemOperand FieldMemOperand(Register object, int offset) {
21 return MemOperand(object, offset - kHeapObjectTag);
22}
23
24// Provides access to exit frame parameters (GC-ed).
25MemOperand ExitFrameStackSlotOperand(int offset) {
26 // The slot at [sp] is reserved in all ExitFrames for storing the return
27 // address before doing the actual call, it's necessary for frame iteration
28 // (see StoreReturnAddressAndCall for details).
29 static constexpr int kSPOffset = 1 * kSystemPointerSize;
30 return MemOperand(sp, kSPOffset + offset);
31}
32
33// Provides access to exit frame parameters (GC-ed).
34MemOperand ExitFrameCallerStackSlotOperand(int index) {
35 return MemOperand(fp, (ExitFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp + index) *
36 kSystemPointerSize);
37}

100void MacroAssembler::Ccmp(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand,
101 StatusFlags nzcv, Condition cond) {
102 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
103 if (operand.IsImmediate() && (operand.ImmediateValue() < 0)) {
104 ConditionalCompareMacro(rn, -operand.ImmediateValue(), nzcv, cond, CCMN);
105 } else {
106 ConditionalCompareMacro(rn, operand, nzcv, cond, CCMP);
107 }
108}
109
110void MacroAssembler::CcmpTagged(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand,
111 StatusFlags nzcv, Condition cond) {
112 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
113 Ccmp(rn.W(), operand.ToW(), nzcv, cond);
114 } else {
115 Ccmp(rn, operand, nzcv, cond);
116 }
117}
118
119void MacroAssembler::Ccmn(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand,
120 StatusFlags nzcv, Condition cond) {
121 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
122 if (operand.IsImmediate() && (operand.ImmediateValue() < 0)) {
123 ConditionalCompareMacro(rn, -operand.ImmediateValue(), nzcv, cond, CCMP);
124 } else {
125 ConditionalCompareMacro(rn, operand, nzcv, cond, CCMN);
126 }
127}

129void MacroAssembler::Add(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
130 const Operand& operand) {
131 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
132 if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
133 int64_t imm = operand.ImmediateValue();
134 if ((imm > 0) && IsImmAddSub(imm)) {
135 DataProcImmediate(rd, rn, static_cast<int>(imm), ADD);
136 return;
137 } else if ((imm < 0) && IsImmAddSub(-imm)) {
138 DataProcImmediate(rd, rn, static_cast<int>(-imm), SUB);
139 return;
140 }
141 } else if (operand.IsShiftedRegister() && (operand.shift_amount() == 0)) {
142 if (!rd.IsSP() && !rn.IsSP() && !operand.reg().IsSP() &&
143 !operand.reg().IsZero()) {
144 DataProcPlainRegister(rd, rn, operand.reg(), ADD);
145 return;
146 }
147 }
148 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, operand, LeaveFlags, ADD);
149}
150
151void MacroAssembler::Adds(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
152 const Operand& operand) {
153 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
154 if (operand.IsImmediate() && (operand.ImmediateValue() < 0) &&
155 IsImmAddSub(-operand.ImmediateValue())) {
156 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, -operand.ImmediateValue(), SetFlags, SUB);
157 } else {
158 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, operand, SetFlags, ADD);
159 }
160}
161
162void MacroAssembler::Sub(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
163 const Operand& operand) {
164 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
165 if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
166 int64_t imm = operand.ImmediateValue();
167 if ((imm > 0) && IsImmAddSub(imm)) {
168 DataProcImmediate(rd, rn, static_cast<int>(imm), SUB);
169 return;
170 } else if ((imm < 0) && IsImmAddSub(-imm)) {
171 DataProcImmediate(rd, rn, static_cast<int>(-imm), ADD);
172 return;
173 }
174 } else if (operand.IsShiftedRegister() && (operand.shift_amount() == 0)) {
175 if (!rd.IsSP() && !rn.IsSP() && !operand.reg().IsSP() &&
176 !operand.reg().IsZero()) {
177 DataProcPlainRegister(rd, rn, operand.reg(), SUB);
178 return;
179 }
180 }
181 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, operand, LeaveFlags, SUB);
182}
183
184void MacroAssembler::Subs(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
185 const Operand& operand) {
186 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
187 if (operand.IsImmediate() && (operand.ImmediateValue() < 0) &&
188 IsImmAddSub(-operand.ImmediateValue())) {
189 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, -operand.ImmediateValue(), SetFlags, ADD);
190 } else {
191 AddSubMacro(rd, rn, operand, SetFlags, SUB);
192 }
193}

197 Adds(AppropriateZeroRegFor(rn), rn, operand);

200void MacroAssembler::Cmp(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand) {
201 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
202 if (operand.IsShiftedRegister() && operand.shift_amount() == 0) {
203 if (!rn.IsSP() && !operand.reg().IsSP()) {
204 CmpPlainRegister(rn, operand.reg());
205 return;
206 }
207 }
208 Subs(AppropriateZeroRegFor(rn), rn, operand);
209}
210
211void MacroAssembler::CmpTagged(const Register& rn, const Operand& operand) {
212 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
213 Cmp(rn.W(), operand.ToW());
214 } else {
215 Cmp(rn, operand);
216 }
217}

219void MacroAssembler::Neg(const Register& rd, const Operand& operand) {
220 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
221 DCHECK(!rd.IsZero());
222 if (operand.IsImmediate()) {
223 Mov(rd, -operand.ImmediateValue());
224 } else {
225 Sub(rd, AppropriateZeroRegFor(rd), operand);
226 }
227}

229void MacroAssembler::Negs(const Register& rd, const Operand& operand) {
230 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
231 Subs(rd, AppropriateZeroRegFor(rd), operand);
232}

400void MacroAssembler::Bind(Label* label, BranchTargetIdentifier id) {
401 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
402 if (id == BranchTargetIdentifier::kNone) {
403 bind(label);
404 } else {
405 // Emit this inside an InstructionAccurateScope to ensure there are no extra
406 // instructions between the bind and the target identifier instruction.
407 InstructionAccurateScope scope(this, 1);
408 bind(label);
409 if (id == BranchTargetIdentifier::kPacibsp) {
410 pacibsp();
411 } else {
412 bti(id);
413 }
414 }
415}

525// Conditionally zero the destination register. Only X registers are supported
526// due to the truncation side-effect when used on W registers.
527void MacroAssembler::CzeroX(const Register& rd, Condition cond) {
528 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
529 DCHECK(!rd.IsSP() && rd.Is64Bits());
530 DCHECK((cond != al) && (cond != nv));
531 csel(rd, xzr, rd, cond);
532}
533
534// Conditionally move a value into the destination register. Only X registers
535// are supported due to the truncation side-effect when used on W registers.
536void MacroAssembler::CmovX(const Register& rd, const Register& rn,
537 Condition cond) {
538 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
539 DCHECK(!rd.IsSP());
540 DCHECK(rd.Is64Bits() && rn.Is64Bits());
541 DCHECK((cond != al) && (cond != nv));
542 if (rd != rn) {
543 csel(rd, rn, rd, cond);
544 }
545}

630void MacroAssembler::Fccmp(const VRegister& fn, const double value,
631 StatusFlags nzcv, Condition cond) {
632 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
633 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
634 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(fn);
635 Fmov(tmp, value);
636 Fccmp(fn, tmp, nzcv, cond);
637}
638
639void MacroAssembler::Fcmp(const VRegister& fn, const VRegister& fm) {
640 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
641 fcmp(fn, fm);
642}
643
644void MacroAssembler::Fcmp(const VRegister& fn, double value) {
645 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
646 if (value != 0.0) {
647 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
648 VRegister tmp = temps.AcquireSameSizeAs(fn);
649 Fmov(tmp, value);
650 fcmp(fn, tmp);
651 } else {
652 fcmp(fn, value);
653 }
654}

751void MacroAssembler::Fmov(VRegister fd, VRegister fn) {
752 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
753 // Only emit an instruction if fd and fn are different, and they are both D
754 // registers. fmov(s0, s0) is not a no-op because it clears the top word of
755 // d0. Technically, fmov(d0, d0) is not a no-op either because it clears the
756 // top of q0, but VRegister does not currently support Q registers.
757 if (fd != fn || !fd.Is64Bits()) {
758 fmov(fd, fn);
759 }
760}
761
762void MacroAssembler::Fmov(VRegister fd, Register rn) {
763 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
764 fmov(fd, rn);
765}
766
767void MacroAssembler::Fmov(VRegister vd, double imm) {
768 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
769 uint64_t bits = base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(imm);
770
771 if (bits == 0) {
772 Movi(vd.D(), 0);
773 return;
774 }
775
776 if (vd.Is1S() || vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S()) {
777 Fmov(vd, static_cast<float>(imm));
778 return;
779 }
780
781 DCHECK(vd.Is1D() || vd.Is2D());
782 if (IsImmFP64(bits)) {
783 fmov(vd, imm);
784 } else {
785 Movi64bitHelper(vd, bits);
786 }
787}
788
789void MacroAssembler::Fmov(VRegister vd, float imm) {
790 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
791 uint32_t bits = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(imm);
792
793 if (bits == 0) {
794 Movi(vd.D(), 0);
795 return;
796 }
797
798 if (vd.Is1D() || vd.Is2D()) {
799 Fmov(vd, static_cast<double>(imm));
800 return;
801 }
802
803 DCHECK(vd.Is1S() || vd.Is2S() || vd.Is4S());
804 if (IsImmFP32(bits)) {
805 fmov(vd, imm);
806 } else if (vd.IsScalar()) {
807 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
808 Register tmp = temps.AcquireW();
809 Mov(tmp, bits);
810 Fmov(vd, tmp);
811 } else {
812 Movi(vd, bits);
813 }
814}

817 DCHECK(allow_macro_instructions());
818 DCHECK(!rd.IsZero());
819 fmov(rd, fn);
820}

1136void MacroAssembler::InitializeRootRegister() {
1137 ExternalReference isolate_root = ExternalReference::isolate_root(isolate());
1138 Mov(kRootRegister, Operand(isolate_root));
1139 Fmov(fp_zero, 0.0);
1140
1141#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1142 LoadRootRelative(kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, IsolateData::cage_base_offset());
1143#endif

1146void MacroAssembler::SmiTag(Register dst, Register src) {
1147 DCHECK(dst.Is64Bits() && src.Is64Bits());
1148 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1149 Lsl(dst, src, kSmiShift);
1150}
1151
1152void MacroAssembler::SmiTag(Register smi) { SmiTag(smi, smi); }
1153
1154void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, Register src) {
1155 DCHECK(dst.Is64Bits() && src.Is64Bits());
1156 if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
1157 AssertSmi(src);
1158 }
1159 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1160 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1161 Sbfx(dst, src.W(), kSmiShift, kSmiValueSize);
1162 } else {
1163 Asr(dst, src, kSmiShift);
1164 }
1165}
1166
1167void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
1168 DCHECK(dst.Is64Bits());
1169 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
1170 if (src.IsImmediateOffset() && src.shift_amount() == 0) {
1171 // Load value directly from the upper half-word.
1172 // Assumes that Smis are shifted by 32 bits and little endianness.
1173 DCHECK_EQ(kSmiShift, 32);
1174 Ldrsw(dst,
1175 MemOperand(src.base(), src.offset() + (kSmiShift / kBitsPerByte),
1176 src.addrmode()));
1177
1178 } else {
1179 Ldr(dst, src);
1180 SmiUntag(dst);
1181 }
1182 } else {
1183 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1184 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1185 Ldr(dst.W(), src);
1186 } else {
1187 Ldr(dst, src);
1188 }
1189 SmiUntag(dst);
1190 }
1191}
1192
1193void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register smi) { SmiUntag(smi, smi); }
1194
1195void MacroAssembler::SmiToInt32(Register smi) { SmiToInt32(smi, smi); }
1196
1197void MacroAssembler::SmiToInt32(Register dst, Register smi) {
1198 DCHECK(dst.Is64Bits());
1199 if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
1200 AssertSmi(smi);
1201 }
1202 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre32Bits() || SmiValuesAre31Bits());
1203 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1204 Asr(dst.W(), smi.W(), kSmiShift);
1205 } else {
1206 Lsr(dst, smi, kSmiShift);
1207 }
1208}

1210void MacroAssembler::JumpIfSmi(Register value, Label* smi_label,
1211 Label* not_smi_label) {
1212 static_assert((kSmiTagSize == 1) && (kSmiTag == 0));
1213 // Check if the tag bit is set.
1214 if (smi_label) {
1215 Tbz(value, 0, smi_label);
1216 if (not_smi_label) {
1217 B(not_smi_label);
1218 }
1219 } else {
1220 DCHECK(not_smi_label);
1221 Tbnz(value, 0, not_smi_label);
1222 }
1223}

1225void MacroAssembler::JumpIfEqual(Register x, int32_t y, Label* dest) {
1226 CompareAndBranch(x, y, eq, dest);
1227}
1228
1229void MacroAssembler::JumpIfLessThan(Register x, int32_t y, Label* dest) {
1230 CompareAndBranch(x, y, lt, dest);
1231}
1232
1233void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotSmi(Register value, Label* not_smi_label) {
1234 JumpIfSmi(value, nullptr, not_smi_label);
1235}

1245template <MacroAssembler::StoreLRMode lr_mode>
1246void MacroAssembler::Push(const CPURegister& src0, const CPURegister& src1,
1247 const CPURegister& src2, const CPURegister& src3) {
1248 DCHECK(AreSameSizeAndType(src0, src1, src2, src3));
1249 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kSignLR), ((src0 == lr) || (src1 == lr) ||
1250 (src2 == lr) || (src3 == lr)));
1251 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kDontStoreLR), ((src0 != lr) && (src1 != lr) &&
1252 (src2 != lr) && (src3 != lr)));
1253
1254#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
1255 if (lr_mode == kSignLR) {
1256 Pacibsp();
1257 }
1258#endif
1259
1260 int count = 1 + src1.is_valid() + src2.is_valid() + src3.is_valid();
1261 int size = src0.SizeInBytes();
1262 DCHECK_EQ(0, (size * count) % 16);
1263
1264 PushHelper(count, size, src0, src1, src2, src3);
1265}
1266
1267template <MacroAssembler::StoreLRMode lr_mode>
1268void MacroAssembler::Push(const Register& src0, const VRegister& src1) {
1269 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kSignLR), ((src0 == lr) || (src1 == lr)));
1270 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kDontStoreLR), ((src0 != lr) && (src1 != lr)));
1271#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
1272 if (lr_mode == kSignLR) {
1273 Pacibsp();
1274 }
1275#endif
1276
1277 int size = src0.SizeInBytes() + src1.SizeInBytes();
1278 DCHECK_EQ(0, size % 16);
1279
1280 // Reserve room for src0 and push src1.
1281 str(src1, MemOperand(sp, -size, PreIndex));
1282 // Fill the gap with src0.
1283 str(src0, MemOperand(sp, src1.SizeInBytes()));
1284}
1285
1286template <MacroAssembler::LoadLRMode lr_mode>
1287void MacroAssembler::Pop(const CPURegister& dst0, const CPURegister& dst1,
1288 const CPURegister& dst2, const CPURegister& dst3) {
1289 // It is not valid to pop into the same register more than once in one
1290 // instruction, not even into the zero register.
1291 DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst0, dst1, dst2, dst3));
1292 DCHECK(AreSameSizeAndType(dst0, dst1, dst2, dst3));
1293 DCHECK(dst0.is_valid());
1294
1295 int count = 1 + dst1.is_valid() + dst2.is_valid() + dst3.is_valid();
1296 int size = dst0.SizeInBytes();
1297 DCHECK_EQ(0, (size * count) % 16);
1298
1299 PopHelper(count, size, dst0, dst1, dst2, dst3);
1300
1301 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kAuthLR), ((dst0 == lr) || (dst1 == lr) ||
1302 (dst2 == lr) || (dst3 == lr)));
1303 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kDontLoadLR), ((dst0 != lr) && (dst1 != lr)) &&
1304 (dst2 != lr) && (dst3 != lr));
1305
1306#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
1307 if (lr_mode == kAuthLR) {
1308 Autibsp();
1309 }
1310#endif
1311}
1312
1313template <MacroAssembler::StoreLRMode lr_mode>
1314void MacroAssembler::Poke(const CPURegister& src, const Operand& offset) {
1315 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kSignLR), (src == lr));
1316 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kDontStoreLR), (src != lr));
1317#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
1318 if (lr_mode == kSignLR) {
1319 Pacibsp();
1320 }
1321#endif
1322
1323 if (offset.IsImmediate()) {
1324 DCHECK_GE(offset.ImmediateValue(), 0);
1325 } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1326 Cmp(xzr, offset);
1327 Check(le, AbortReason::kStackAccessBelowStackPointer);
1328 }
1329
1330 Str(src, MemOperand(sp, offset));
1331}
1332
1333template <MacroAssembler::LoadLRMode lr_mode>
1334void MacroAssembler::Peek(const CPURegister& dst, const Operand& offset) {
1335 if (offset.IsImmediate()) {
1336 DCHECK_GE(offset.ImmediateValue(), 0);
1337 } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
1338 Cmp(xzr, offset);
1339 Check(le, AbortReason::kStackAccessBelowStackPointer);
1340 }
1341
1342 Ldr(dst, MemOperand(sp, offset));
1343
1344 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kAuthLR), (dst == lr));
1345 DCHECK_IMPLIES((lr_mode == kDontLoadLR), (dst != lr));
1346#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTROL_FLOW_INTEGRITY
1347 if (lr_mode == kAuthLR) {
1348 Autibsp();
1349 }
1350#endif
1351}

1353void MacroAssembler::Claim(int64_t count, uint64_t unit_size) {
1354 DCHECK_GE(count, 0);
1355 uint64_t size = count * unit_size;
1356
1357 if (size == 0) {
1358 return;
1359 }
1360 DCHECK_EQ(size % 16, 0);
1361#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
1362 while (size > kStackPageSize) {
1363 Sub(sp, sp, kStackPageSize);
1364 Str(xzr, MemOperand(sp));
1365 size -= kStackPageSize;
1366 }
1367#endif
1368 Sub(sp, sp, size);
1369}
1370
1371void MacroAssembler::Claim(const Register& count, uint64_t unit_size,
1372 bool assume_sp_aligned) {
1373 if (unit_size == 0) return;
1374 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(unit_size));
1375
1376 const int shift = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(unit_size);
1377 const Operand size(count, LSL, shift);
1378
1379 if (size.IsZero()) {
1380 return;
1381 }
1382 AssertPositiveOrZero(count);
1383
1384#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_WIN
1385 // "Functions that allocate 4k or more worth of stack must ensure that each
1386 // page prior to the final page is touched in order." Source:
1387 // https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/build/arm64-windows-abi-conventions?view=vs-2019#stack
1388
1389 // Callers expect count register to not be clobbered, so copy it.
1390 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1391 Register bytes_scratch = temps.AcquireX();
1392 Mov(bytes_scratch, size);
1393
1394 Label check_offset;
1395 Label touch_next_page;
1396 B(&check_offset);
1397 Bind(&touch_next_page);
1398 Sub(sp, sp, kStackPageSize);
1399 // Just to touch the page, before we increment further.
1400 if (assume_sp_aligned) {
1401 Str(xzr, MemOperand(sp));
1402 } else {
1403 Register sp_copy = temps.AcquireX();
1404 Mov(sp_copy, sp);
1405 Str(xzr, MemOperand(sp_copy));
1406 }
1407 Sub(bytes_scratch, bytes_scratch, kStackPageSize);
1408
1409 Bind(&check_offset);
1410 Cmp(bytes_scratch, kStackPageSize);
1411 B(gt, &touch_next_page);
1412
1413 Sub(sp, sp, bytes_scratch);
1414#else
1415 Sub(sp, sp, size);
1416#endif
1417}

1419void MacroAssembler::Drop(int64_t count, uint64_t unit_size) {
1420 DCHECK_GE(count, 0);
1421 uint64_t size = count * unit_size;
1422
1423 if (size == 0) {
1424 return;
1425 }
1426
1427 Add(sp, sp, size);
1428 DCHECK_EQ(size % 16, 0);
1429}

1431void MacroAssembler::Drop(const Register& count, uint64_t unit_size) {
1432 if (unit_size == 0) return;
1433 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(unit_size));
1434
1435 const int shift = base::bits::CountTrailingZeros(unit_size);
1436 const Operand size(count, LSL, shift);
1437
1438 if (size.IsZero()) {
1439 return;
1440 }
1441
1442 AssertPositiveOrZero(count);
1443 Add(sp, sp, size);
1444}

1446void MacroAssembler::DropArguments(const Register& count,
1447 ArgumentsCountMode mode) {
1448 int extra_slots = 1; // Padding slot.
1449 if (mode == kCountExcludesReceiver) {
1450 // Add a slot for the receiver.
1451 ++extra_slots;
1452 }
1453 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1454 Register tmp = temps.AcquireX();
1455 Add(tmp, count, extra_slots);
1456 Bic(tmp, tmp, 1);
1457 Drop(tmp, kXRegSize);
1458}

1460void MacroAssembler::DropArguments(int64_t count, ArgumentsCountMode mode) {
1461 if (mode == kCountExcludesReceiver) {
1462 // Add a slot for the receiver.
1463 ++count;
1464 }
1465 Drop(RoundUp(count, 2), kXRegSize);
1466}

1474void MacroAssembler::CompareAndBranch(const Register& lhs, const Operand& rhs,
1475 Condition cond, Label* label) {
1476 if (rhs.IsImmediate() && (rhs.ImmediateValue() == 0)) {
1477 switch (cond) {
1478 case eq:
1479 case ls:
1480 Cbz(lhs, label);
1481 return;
1482 case lt:
1483 Tbnz(lhs, lhs.SizeInBits() - 1, label);
1484 return;
1485 case ge:
1486 Tbz(lhs, lhs.SizeInBits() - 1, label);
1487 return;
1488 case ne:
1489 case hi:
1490 Cbnz(lhs, label);
1491 return;
1492 default:
1493 break;
1494 }
1495 }
1496 Cmp(lhs, rhs);
1497 B(cond, label);
1498}

1500void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(const Register& lhs,
1501 const Operand& rhs, Condition cond,
1502 Label* label) {
1503 if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
1504 CompareAndBranch(lhs.W(), rhs.ToW(), cond, label);
1505 } else {
1506 CompareAndBranch(lhs, rhs, cond, label);
1507 }
1508}

1510void MacroAssembler::TestAndBranchIfAnySet(const Register& reg,
1511 const uint64_t bit_pattern,
1512 Label* label) {
1513 int bits = reg.SizeInBits();
1514 DCHECK_GT(CountSetBits(bit_pattern, bits), 0);
1515 if (CountSetBits(bit_pattern, bits) == 1) {
1516 Tbnz(reg, MaskToBit(bit_pattern), label);
1517 } else {
1518 Tst(reg, bit_pattern);
1519 B(ne, label);
1520 }
1521}

1523void MacroAssembler::TestAndBranchIfAllClear(const Register& reg,
1524 const uint64_t bit_pattern,
1525 Label* label) {
1526 int bits = reg.SizeInBits();
1527 DCHECK_GT(CountSetBits(bit_pattern, bits), 0);
1528 if (CountSetBits(bit_pattern, bits) == 1) {
1529 Tbz(reg, MaskToBit(bit_pattern), label);
1530 } else {
1531 Tst(reg, bit_pattern);
1532 B(eq, label);
1533 }
